issue.body:
Bumps [@storybook/addon-essentials](https://github.com/storybookjs/storybook/tree/HEAD/code/addons/essentials) from 8.5.8 to 8.6.14.
Release notes

Sourced from @â€‹storybook/addon-essentials's releases.

v8.6.14

8.6.14

  • CLI: Add skip onboarding, recommended/minimal config - #30930, thanks @â€‹shilman!
  • Core: Fix using dates in expect statements - #28413, thanks @â€‹yann-combarnous!
  • React Native Web: Fix expo router by setting JSX to automatic - #31484, thanks @â€‹dannyhw!
  • Test: Make sure that lit arrays are not cloned - #31435, thanks @â€‹kasperpeulen!

v8.6.13

8.6.13

  • Controls: Fix boxShadow on empty controls - #27193, thanks @â€‹H0onnn!
  • React Native Web: Update react-native-web - #31324, thanks @â€‹ndelangen!

v8.6.12

8.6.12

  • CLI: Only install Visual Test Addon if test feature is selected - #30966, thanks @â€‹ghengeveld!
  • Core: Fix telemetry error on Storybook UI - #30953, thanks @â€‹yannbf!
  • Ember: Fix ember-template-compiler import for ember 6+ - #30682, thanks @â€‹leoeuclids!
  • Next: Upgrade vite-plugin-storybook-nextjs for Next v14 compatibility - #30997, thanks @â€‹kasperpeulen!
  • Svelte: Exclude node_modules from docgen - #30981, thanks @â€‹JReinhold!

v8.6.11

8.6.11

  • Angular: Fix zone.js support for Angular libraries - #30941, thanks @â€‹valentinpalkovic!

v8.6.10

  • Nextjs: Fix styled-jsx optimize vite warnings - #30932, thanks @â€‹kasperpeulen!
  • React: Fix actImplementation is not a function - #30929, thanks @â€‹kasperpeulen!

v8.6.9

8.6.9

  • Next: Fix react aliases in next vite plugin - #30914, thanks @â€‹kasperpeulen!

v8.6.8

8.6.8

  • Angular: Export all files in Angular package.json - #30849, thanks @â€‹kasperpeulen!
  • CLI: Don't add packageManager entry to package.json automatically - #30855, thanks @â€‹kasperpeulen!
  • React: Allow portable stories to be used in SSR - #30847, thanks @â€‹kasperpeulen!
  • Svelte: Adjust Svelte typings to include Svelte 5 function components - #30852, thanks @â€‹dummdidumm!
  • Telemetry: Make sure that telemetry doesn't fail on init - #30857, thanks @â€‹kasperpeulen!

issue.title: Implement zero-copy FFI transfer of batches from JVM to Native
issue.body:
### What is the problem the feature request solves?

Comet doesn't currently follow Arrow best practice when transferring batches from JVM to native code. Ownership is retained by the JVM after batches have been made available in FFI, requiring a copy to be made on the native side. 

It would be better to pass ownership of batches to native rather than make copies.

This design was necessary originally due to the use of mutable Parquet buffers in the `native_comet` Parquet scan.

### Describe the potential solution

Once https://github.com/apache/datafusion-comet/issues/2152 is implemented, and once we have removed the `native_comet` scan and all uses of mutable Parquet buffers, we should be able to implement zero-copy FFI.

### Additional context

_No response_
